<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The cascadeDelete() method works only when the delete operation is performed over a Zend_Db_Table_Row. For instance it works successfully in the following case:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$table = new Application_Model_DbTable_Sample();
$table-&gt;find(12)-&gt;current()-&gt;delete();
</code></pre>

<p>but it does not work for:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$table = new Application_Model_DbTable_Sample();
$table-&gt;delete('id=?',12);
</code></pre>

<p>seems like a bug, right?</p>

